"use strict";(self.webpackChunk_dreamcatcher_tech_dreamcatcher_website=self.webpackChunk_dreamcatcher_tech_dreamcatcher_website||[]).push([[659],{27997:(e,t,n)=>{n.r(t),n.d(t,{assets:()=>c,contentTitle:()=>r,default:()=>p,frontMatter:()=>o,metadata:()=>s,toc:()=>h});var i=n(87462),a=(n(67294),n(3905));const o={published:!1,title:"The Network is the Innovator",description:""},r=void 0,s={permalink:"/blog/2022/05/22/ The Network is the Innovator",editUrl:"https://github.com/dreamcatcher-tech/dreamcatcher-tech.github.io/edit/master/website/blog/2022-05-22 The Network is the Innovator.md",source:"@site/blog/2022-05-22 The Network is the Innovator.md",title:"The Network is the Innovator",description:"",date:"2022-05-22T00:00:00.000Z",formattedDate:"May 22, 2022",tags:[],readingTime:2.195,hasTruncateMarker:!1,authors:[],frontMatter:{published:!1,title:"The Network is the Innovator",description:""},prevItem:{title:"Packet Switched Invention Networks",permalink:"/blog/2022/08/22/packet-switched-invention-networks"},nextItem:{title:"Blockchain Without Currency",permalink:"/blog/2022/05/14/blockchain-without-currency"}},c={authorsImageUrls:[]},h=[],l={toc:h};function p(e){let{components:t,...o}=e;return(0,a.kt)("wrapper",(0,i.Z)({},l,o,{components:t,mdxType:"MDXLayout"}),(0,a.kt)("p",null,(0,a.kt)("em",{parentName:"p"},'"Revolutionizing the Digital Landscape: Inverted Apps, Championing Consumer-Centric Operation"')),(0,a.kt)("p",null,(0,a.kt)("img",{alt:"bing: an image of a application that has been inverted to serve its consumers rather than its controllers, in the form a swarm of robotic production lines with a colorful starburst as its backdrop",src:n(95794).Z,width:"1024",height:"1024"})),(0,a.kt)("h1",{id:"exploring-packet-switched-innovation-networks"},"Exploring Packet-Switched Innovation Networks"),(0,a.kt)("p",null,"In our interconnected world, analogies can often provide insightful perspectives. One such analogy can be drawn between packet-switched networks, circuit-switched networks, dedicated lines, and the evolution of innovation networks."),(0,a.kt)("p",null,"For those unfamiliar with the concept, packet-switching is a method of grouping data that is transmitted over a digital network into packets. These packets are then independently routed to their destination, where they are reassembled. This method contrasts with circuit-switching, where a dedicated communication path is established between two points, and all data follows this single path. "),(0,a.kt)("p",null,"Applying these concepts to innovation networks, we can view each innovation or idea as a packet of information. These packets are transmitted within the network, encountering various routes, obstacles, and changes along the way. "),(0,a.kt)("p",null,"However, packet-switched networks aren't perfect, and they present two major challenges:"),(0,a.kt)("ol",null,(0,a.kt)("li",{parentName:"ol"},(0,a.kt)("p",{parentName:"li"},(0,a.kt)("strong",{parentName:"p"},"Discontinuity:")," Just as packets may arrive at the destination out of order, ideas within an innovation network can be disjointed or lack cohesion. ")),(0,a.kt)("li",{parentName:"ol"},(0,a.kt)("p",{parentName:"li"},(0,a.kt)("strong",{parentName:"p"},"Conversions:")," Much like data packets need to be formatted and checked for errors (checksumming) before transmission, innovations often require formalization and validation before they can be implemented. This process can be slow and cumbersome, potentially stifling the pace of innovation."))),(0,a.kt)("p",null,"Despite these challenges, the benefits of a packet-switched approach to innovation are notable. By embracing the inherent discontinuity and conversion processes, we can create an innovation network that is dynamic, resilient, and adaptive. "),(0,a.kt)("p",null,"In this model, the network itself becomes the innovator. It's not about any single entity driving change, but rather the collective effort of the network, with each node contributing to the overall innovation."),(0,a.kt)("p",null,"We can visualize the innovation process as a series of information circuits, each with its unique challenges and opportunities. These circuits may have unreliable operation, delays, lost packets (unrealized ideas), and varying costs. "),(0,a.kt)("p",null,"However, just as in a packet-switched network, the ability to break down a large packet (or idea) into smaller pieces, transport them via alternate routes, and reassemble them at the destination can prove to be highly effective. This approach allows for parallel processing, resilience in the face of obstacles, and the integration of diverse perspectives."),(0,a.kt)("p",null,"In conclusion, viewing innovation through the lens of packet-switching networks opens up exciting possibilities for the way we conceptualize, manage, and execute innovation. By embracing the network as the innovator, we can build a more resilient, adaptive, and efficient innovation ecosystem\u30105\u2020source\u3011."))}p.isMDXComponent=!0},95794:(e,t,n)=>{n.d(t,{Z:()=>i});const i=n.p+"assets/images/2023-05-23-inverted-apps-dawn-1f92da589c5d92a6f99910260a7420fb.jpeg"}}]);